Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lime{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and a dash of @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} (save the rest for serving). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano and onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add half the @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step) and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Meanwhile, rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Push veggies to one side of pan; add a drizzle of oil to empty side. Add shrimp and remaining Fajita Spice. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp is opaque and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir veggies and shrimp to combine. Add a big squeeze of lime juice and season with salt and pepper to taste. Turn off heat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, about ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with shrimp and veggie filling and spicy guacamole. Drizzle with @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon}. Serve with remaining hot sauce and any remaining lime wedges on the side.